relevant_findings.general: Well appearing elderly woman in NAD
relevant_findings.eyes: extra-ocular movements intact, pupils equal round, reactive to light, sclera anicteric, not injected, no exudates; right eye covered with clear patch
relevant_findings.ENT: mucous membranes moist, no ulcerations or exudates
relevant_findings.cardiovascular: regular rate and rhythm, normal S1, S2, no murmurs, rubs or gallops
relevant_findings.respiratory: clear to auscultation bilaterally, no wheezes, rales or rhonchi
relevant_findings.abdomen: multiple well healed surgical incisions, soft, diffusely tender to palpation with guarding but no rebound, slightly distended, no hepatosplenomegaly, bowel sounds present
relevant_findings.extremities: no cyanosis, clubbing, edema, joint swelling
relevant_findings.neurological: alert and oriented x3, cranial nerves II-XII intact, normal attention, sensation normal, asterixis absent, speech fluent, DTR's 2+ bilaterally
relevant_findings.integument: warm, moist, no ulceration, bilateral lower extremities with patchy hyperpigmentation
